Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{P}^{N}(k)=\mathbb{P}^{(n+1)(m+1)-1}$
\end_inset

 be projective space with homogeneous coordinates 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{i,j}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq i\leq n$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq j\leq m$
\end_inset

.
 There is an obviously well-defined set-theoretic map 
\begin_inset Formula $f:\mathbb{P}^{n}(k)\times\mathbb{P}^{m}(k)\to\mathbb{P}^{N}(k)$
\end_inset

 given by 
\begin_inset Formula $z_{i,j}=x_{i}y_{j}$
\end_inset

.
 
